Package com.commander4j.messages

The com.commander4j.messages package contains a class for each type of inbound and outbound message.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GenericMessageHeader
    All Commander4j xml messages have a standard format.
    IncommingBatchStatusChange
    IncommingBatchStatusChange class allows an external system to update the APP_MATERIAL_BATCH table.
    IncommingDespatchConfirmation
    IncommingDespatchConfirmation class allows an external system to generate a despatch transaction.
    IncommingInspectionResult  
    IncommingJourney
    IncommingJourney class allows an external system to generate a despatch transaction.
    IncommingLocation
    IncommingLocation creates or updates records in the APP_LOCATION table.
    IncommingMaterialAutoMove
    IncommingMaterialAutoMove is used to update 2 fields of the Material Master MoveAfterMakeEnabled and MoveAfterMakeLocationID
    IncommingMaterialDefinition
    IncommingMaterialDefinition allows material master data to be imported from an external system.
    IncommingPalletImportXML  
    IncommingPalletMove
    IncommingPalletMove as its name suggests updates the Pallet Location.
    IncommingPalletStatusChange
    IncommingPalletStatusChange as its name suggests updates the Pallet Status.
    IncommingProcessOrder
    IncommingProcessOrder creates or updates records in the APP_PROCESS_ORDER table.
    IncommingProcessOrderStatusChange
    IncommingProcessOrderStatusChange updates records in the APP_PROCESS_ORDER table.
    IncommingProductionDeclarationConfirmation
    IncommingProductionDeclarationConfirmation allows an external system (typically an auto-labeller) to declare a pallet (SSCC) as being created - successfully labelled.
    IncommingQMInspectionRequest  
    OutgoingDespatchConfirmation  
    OutgoingDespatchEmail  
    OutgoingDespatchPreAdvice  
    OutgoingEquipmentTracking  
    OutgoingPalletDelete  
    OutgoingPalletExportXML  
    OutgoingPalletSplit  
    OutgoingPalletStatusChange  
    OutgoingProductionDeclarationConfirmation
    The OutgoingProductionDeclarationConfirmation message is designed to output a message to an external system (typically an ERP system) to inform it that a pallet (SSCC) has been created and record production.
